line_1: And see, IBERIA bleeds! while Vict'ry twines
line_2: Her fairest garlands round PERUVIA'S shrines;

line_1: Once more the leaf expands, the drooping tendril twines.
line_2: Thus when some tender plant neglected pines,

line_1: Once more the leaf expands, the drooping tendril twines.
line_2: How soon refreshed its vivid lustre shines!

line_1: While round her arm unseen a serpent twines —
line_2: O smile accurst, to hide the worst designs!

line_2: "This Sidney knew, who still with lustre shines,

line_1: "There round the warriour's palm the lover's myrtle twines."
line_2: "And many more whose names might grace his lines;

line_1: But if sweet Love with baby-fingers twines,
line_2: And wets with dewy lips the lengthening lines,

line_1: And round its Oak the Ivy closer twines.
line_2: The Husband Elm supports th'embracing Vines,

line_1: The thread which dame Lachesis twines:
line_2: That was spun for my fair Charlotte Lynes.
